Otti Berger (* October 4, 1898 in Zmajevac / Baranja, Hungary; â€  1944/45 in Auschwitz concentration camp) was a textile artist and weaver. She was a student and later teacher at the Bauhaus. Berger was born in Zmajevac, part of present-day Croatia. Berger had Yugoslav citizenship, but is often credited among Hungarian artists.


